- So `p` has *no sink* in this function — no release operation targets `p` itself.

Therefore, for all paths where `p` is acquired at line 4:
- There is *no propagation* of `p` to any sink (no `p.destroy()`, etc.).
- There is *no propagation* to any argument (no call site passes `p`).
