The only possible release context would be if `p` were cleaned up implicitly, but per Java semantics: `Process` objects *must be explicitly destroyed or waited for*, otherwise they leak OS process resources. No such call exists.

So all paths have “No propagation”, and guarantee_level = `none`, because there is *zero* release of the process on *any* exit path.

